The paper deals with domain adaptation for semantic image segmentation, which is a problem in computer vision. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also proposes a novel bidirectional learning framework, which involves training two models alternately, and a self-supervised learning algorithm, which falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG and cs.AI). The paper also deals with image translation, which is a subfield of multimedia (cs.MM). Finally, the paper involves semantic segmentation, which is a problem in natural language processing (NLP) as well, and hence, it could also be categorized under cs.CL (Computation and Language).
